13.71	Oath_of_enlistment	United States Armed Forces oath of enlistment	Upon enlisting in the United States Armed Forces, each person enlisting in an armed force (whether a soldier, sailor, airman, or marine) takes an oath of enlistment required by federal statute in 10 U.S.C. ยง 502. That section provides the text of the oath and sets out who may administer the oath:	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Oath_of_enlistment_%C2%B7_DF-ST-91-07705.JPEG/220px-Oath_of_enlistment_%C2%B7_DF-ST-91-07705.JPEG
